<item>
            <title>[HBASE-14061] Support CF-level Storage Policy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14061</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After reading &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12848&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;HBASE-12848&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12934&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;HBASE-12934&lt;/a&gt;, I wrote a patch to implement cf-level storage policy. &lt;br/&gt;
My main purpose is to improve random-read performance for some really hot data, which usually locates in certain column family of a big table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usage:&lt;br/&gt;
$ hbase shell&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; alter &apos;TABLE_NAME&apos;, METADATA =&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;
{&apos;hbase.hstore.block.storage.policy&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;POLICY_NAME&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; alter &apos;TABLE_NAME&apos;, {NAME=&amp;gt;&apos;CF_NAME&apos;, METADATA =&amp;gt; {&apos;hbase.hstore.block.storage.policy&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;POLICY_NAME&apos;}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HDFS&apos;s setStoragePolicy can only take effect when new hfile is created in a configured directory, so I had to make sub directories(for each cf) in region&apos;s .tmp directory and set storage policy for them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides, I had to upgrade hadoop version to 2.6.0 because dfs.getStoragePolicy cannot be easily written in reflection, and I needed this api to finish my unit test.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;hadoop-2.6.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
